
1. Install Cygwin

2. Run Cygwin first time and perform post-install activity


The following commands should be executed one by one. They do:
- Modify /etc/passwd
- Remove the current home dir
- Create soft link to NEW-HOME-DIR

cd "NEW-HOME-DIR"
sed -i "/$USERNAME/ s|^\(.*\):.*:\(.*\)|\1:$(pwd):\2|" /etc/passwd

cd ~/..
rm -rf "$HOME"

ln -s "$OLDPWD" $USERNAME


6. Close the current Cygwin session

